<div class="debug-container">
  <h1>Keycloak Connection Debugger</h1>
  
  <div class="debug-section">
    <h2>Environment Variables</h2>
    <table class="debug-table">
      <tr>
        <th>Variable</th>
        <th>Value</th>
      </tr>
      <% @env_vars.each do |key, value| %>
        <tr>
          <td><strong><%= key %></strong></td>
          <td><code><%= value %></code></td>
        </tr>
      <% end %>
    </table>
  </div>
  
  <div class="debug-section">
    <h2>Connection Test</h2>
    <div class="connection-status <%= @connection_test[:success] ? 'success' : 'error' %>">
      <div class="status-indicator"></div>
      <div class="status-text">
        <%= @connection_test[:success] ? "Connection Successful" : "Connection Failed" %>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <table class="debug-table">
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Status Code</strong></td>
        <td><code><%= @connection_test[:status] %></code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Message</strong></td>
        <td><code><%= @connection_test[:message] %></code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>URL</strong></td>
        <td><code><%= @connection_test[:url] %></code></td>
      </tr>
      <% if @connection_test[:error].present? %>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Error</strong></td>
          <td><code><%= @connection_test[:error] %></code></td>
        </tr>
      <% end %>
    </table>
  </div>
  
  <div class="debug-section">
    <h2>Troubleshooting Tips</h2>
    <div class="tips">
      <p><strong>If you're seeing connection errors:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Make sure your Keycloak server is running and accessible</li>
        <li>Check that KEYCLOAK_URL is correct (should be just the hostname without protocol)</li>
        <li>Verify that the realm exists in your Keycloak instance</li>
        <li>Ensure you've set up proper network access (firewall, DNS, etc.)</li>
        <li>If using localhost, ensure the port is correct (default is 8080)</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p><strong>Common solutions:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>For local development, try using <code>localhost:8080</code> as your KEYCLOAK_URL</li>
        <li>Make sure you're using HTTPS for production environments</li>
        <li>For Docker, ensure port mapping is correctly configured</li>
        <li>If behind a proxy, ensure it's correctly forwarding to Keycloak</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="actions">
    <a href="<%= lobby_path %>" class="btn-primary">Back to Login</a>
  </div>
</div>

